olive oil
½ tin sweetcorn
2 brioche hotdog buns
1 pulled chicken
1 Brioche Hotdog Buns
1 packet Pulled Chicken
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend
1 packet BBQ Sauce
1 packet Mayonnaise
1 packet Dijon Mustard
1 tsp honey
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar

• Drain sweetcorn (see ingredients).
• Slice brioche hotdog buns in half lengthways.
• Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Cook corn kernels until lightly browned, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a large bowl.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the kernels are ‘popping’ out.

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook pulled chicken and All-American spice blend, breaking up with a spoon, until browned,
3-4 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then add BBQ sauce and a splash of water and stir to combine. Season to taste

• Toast brioche hotdog buns as desired.
• In a small bowl combine mayonnaise, Dijon mustard and the honey.
• To the bowl with the corn, add shredded cabbage mix, mixed salad leaves, half the mustard mayonnaise and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Toss to combine and season to taste.

• Spread bun bases with remaining mustard mayonnaise.
• Fill buns with corn slaw and pulled chicken.
• Divide Texan-style BBQ pulled chicken subs between plates.
• Serve with any leftover corn slaw. Enjoy!